<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 03 at 7:23AM MDT  by NWS Glasgow</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern Wibaux
and southeastern Dawson Counties through 830 AM MDT...
At 723 AM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles east of Glendive, moving east at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of northeastern Wibaux
and southeastern Dawson Counties.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
To report severe weather, contact your nearest law enforcement
agency. They will relay your report to the National Weather Service
office in Glasgow.</instruction>
